<record_update table="u_snd_process_flow_style">
    <u_snd_process_flow_style action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <sys_created_by>admin_SHARE</sys_created_by>
        <sys_created_on>2016-04-22 12:44:24</sys_created_on>
        <sys_id>ac08c7f70fb21200bfd60cbce1050e7f</sys_id>
        <sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count>
        <sys_updated_by>tim@sndeveloper.com_SHARE</sys_updated_by>
        <sys_updated_on>2016-04-22 17:08:37</sys_updated_on>
        <u_css>.snd_process_flow {
  text-align:center;
}

.snd_process_flow_list {
  font-size:large;
  border: 2px solid white;
  padding-left:0px;
}

.snd_process_flow_list li {
  background-color: #f0f0f0;
  display:inline-block;
  padding: 4px 15px;
  margin-top: 6px;
  padding-left:40px;
}

.snd_process_flow_list li:after {
  display: inherit;
  height: 25px;
  width: 25px;
  outline:1px solid transparent;
  -webkit-backface-visibility:hidden;
  backface-visibility:hidden;
  -webkit-box-shadow: 1px -1px 0px 0px rgba(255,255,255,1);
  -moz-box-shadow: 1px -1px 0px 0px rgba(255,255,255,1);
  box-shadow: 1px -1px 0px 0px rgba(255,255,255,1);
  margin-left: 4px;
  position: absolute;
  border-top: 2px solid white;
  border-right: 2px solid white;
  content: '';
  -moz-transform: rotate(45deg);
  -ms-transform: rotate(45deg);
  -webkit-transform: rotate(45deg);
  transform: rotate(45deg);
}

.snd_process_flow_list li:last-child:after {
  display: none;
}

.snd_process_flow_list li:last-child {
  padding-right: 25px;
}

.snd_process_flow_list li:first-child {
  padding-left: 25px;
}

.snd_process_flow_list li:hover {
  text-decoration:none;
  cursor:default;
}

.snd_process_flow_list li:hover:after {
  text-decoration:none;
  cursor:pointer;
}

li.selected:hover,
li.select:hover,
li.available:hover,
li.selected:hover:after,
li.select:hover:after,
li.available:hover:after {
  background-color: #00AEEF;
  color:white;
  cursor:pointer;
}

li.selected,
li.selected:after {
  color: white;
  background-color: #54B947;
}

li.select,
li.select:after {
  color:white;
  background-color:#EC008C;
}

li.available,
li.available:after {
  background-color: #f0f0f0;
  color:black;
}

li.unavailable,
li.unavailable:after {
  color:gray;
  background-color:#f0f0f0;
  text-decoration:none;
  cursor:default;
}

li.unavailable:hover,
li.unavailable:hover:after {
  text-decoration:none;
  cursor:default;
}</u_css>
        <u_description>Process flow theme with SN Developer colours, bright & bold.</u_description>
        <u_name>SND - Bright & Bold</u_name>
    </u_snd_process_flow_style>
</record_update>

<record_update table="u_snd_process_flow_style">
    <u_snd_process_flow_style action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <sys_created_by>admin_SHARE</sys_created_by>
        <sys_created_on>2016-04-22 12:44:53</sys_created_on>
        <sys_id>d62847f70fb21200bfd60cbce1050eea</sys_id>
        <sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count>

        <sys_updated_on>2016-04-22 18:39:48</sys_updated_on>
        <u_css>.snd_process_flow {
  text-align:center;
}
.snd_process_flow_list {
  font-size:large;
  border: 2px solid white;
  padding-left:0px;
}

.snd_process_flow_list li {
  background-color: #f0f0f0;
  display:inline-block;
  padding: 4px 15px;
  margin-top: 6px;
  padding-left:25px;
}

.snd_process_flow_list li:after {
  display: inherit;
  height: 25px;
  width: 25px;
  outline:1px solid transparent;
  -webkit-backface-visibility:hidden;
  backface-visibility:hidden;
  -webkit-box-shadow: 1px -1px 0px 0px rgba(255,255,255,1);
  -moz-box-shadow: 1px -1px 0px 0px rgba(255,255,255,1);
  box-shadow: 1px -1px 0px 0px rgba(255,255,255,1);
  margin-left: 4px;
  position: absolute;
  border-top: 2px solid white;
  border-right: 2px solid white;
  content: '';
  -moz-transform: rotate(45deg);
  -ms-transform: rotate(45deg);
  -webkit-transform: rotate(45deg);
  transform: rotate(45deg);
}

.snd_process_flow_list li:last-child:after {
  display: none;
}

.snd_process_flow_list li:hover {
  text-decoration:none;
  cursor:default;
}

.snd_process_flow_list li:hover:after {
  text-decoration:none;
  cursor:pointer;
}

li.selected:hover,
li.select:hover,
li.available:hover {
  border-bottom: 4px solid  #00AEEF;
  color:#00AEEF;
  cursor:pointer;
}

li.selected {
  color: #54B947;
  border-bottom: 4px solid  #54B947;
}

li.select {
  color:#EC008C;
  border-bottom: 4px solid #EC008C;
}

li.available {
  border-bottom: 4px solid  #f0f0f0;
  color:black;
}

li.unavailable,
li.unavailable:after {
  color:gray;
  background-color:#f0f0f0;
  text-decoration:none;
  cursor:default;
}

li.unavailable:hover,
li.unavailable:hover:after {
  text-decoration:none;
  cursor:default;
}</u_css>
        <u_description>Minimilist formatter that just uses text and hovers, no background colours or styles</u_description>
        <u_name>SND - Clean</u_name>
    </u_snd_process_flow_style>
</record_update>

Interactive Process Flow - Quick Start

Welcome to SNDs Interactive Process Flow. Here you can configure clickable process flows simply and quickly

Setting up interactive process flows is easy, just follow these simple steps:

  1. Select a name for your process flow
  2. Select the table that this process flow should run on.
  3. Pick a style for your process flow
  4. Select a display condition using the condition builder. This determines when this process flow should be displayed, allowing you to configure many process flows for one table.

Hit submit and then configure the process flow elements. Once these are configured you're ready to go. Configure the form for the selected table and add the "SND - Interactive Process Flow" formatter.

<record_update table="u_snd_process_flow_style">
    <u_snd_process_flow_style action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <sys_created_by>admin_SHARE</sys_created_by>
        <sys_created_on>2016-04-22 12:44:39</sys_created_on>

        <u_css>.snd_process_flow {
  text-align:center;
}

.snd_process_flow_list {
  font-size:large;
  border: 2px solid white;
  padding-left:0px;
}

.snd_process_flow_list li {
  background-color: #f0f0f0;
  display:inline-block;
  padding: 4px 15px;
  margin-top: 6px;
  padding-left:25px;
}

.snd_process_flow_list li:after {
  display: inherit;
  height: 25px;
  width: 25px;
  outline:1px solid transparent;
  -webkit-backface-visibility:hidden;
  backface-visibility:hidden;
  -webkit-box-shadow: 1px -1px 0px 0px rgba(255,255,255,1);
  -moz-box-shadow: 1px -1px 0px 0px rgba(255,255,255,1);
  box-shadow: 1px -1px 0px 0px rgba(255,255,255,1);
  margin-left: 4px;
  position: absolute;
  border-top: 2px solid white;
  border-right: 2px solid white;
  content: '';
  -moz-transform: rotate(45deg);
  -ms-transform: rotate(45deg);
  -webkit-transform: rotate(45deg);
  transform: rotate(45deg);
}

.snd_process_flow_list li:last-child:after {
  display: none;
}

.snd_process_flow_list li:hover {
  text-decoration:none;
  cursor:default;
}

.snd_process_flow_list li:hover:after {
  text-decoration:none;
  cursor:pointer;
}

li.selected:hover,
li.select:hover,
li.available:hover {
  border-bottom: 4px solid  #00AEEF;
  color:#00AEEF;
  cursor:pointer;
}

li.selected {
  color: #54B947;
  border-bottom: 4px solid  #54B947;
}

li.select {
  color:#EC008C;
  border-bottom: 4px solid #EC008C;
}

li.available {
  border-bottom: 4px solid  #f0f0f0;
  color:black;
}

li.unavailable,
li.unavailable:after {
  color:gray;
  background-color:#f0f0f0;
  text-decoration:none;
  cursor:default;
}

li.unavailable:hover,
li.unavailable:hover:after {
  text-decoration:none;
  cursor:default;
}</u_css>
        <u_description>Mimics the OOTB Process Flow formatter style, but with an SND flavour</u_description>
        <u_name>SND - Classic</u_name>
    </u_snd_process_flow_style>
</record_update>

Interactive Process Flow Elements - Quick Start

Welcome to SNDs Interactive Process Flow Elements. Here you can configure the individual elements that make up a process flow simply and quickly

Setting up process flow elements is easy, just follow these simple steps:

  1. Select a name for your process flow - this is the internal name
  2. Select a label for your process flow element - this text will be displayed to the user
  3. Set the order of this element, the lower the order, the further to the left this element will be displayed
  4. Select a condition that signifies this element is "selected". E.g. if configuring a Resolved element for the incident process flow, the condition would be "state is resolved".

Now we get to the interesting parts! The client script field allows you to add client code which runs when the user clicks this process flow element. Taking the incident resolved example from above, here we would add g_form.setValue('state', 6);

Next we have the Access script. The access script runs server side and controls whether the current user can click a particular process flow element. By default it is set to current.canWrite().
